{
  "stem": "16503.3",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 364.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Now we were thrown out of the cart-- cars-- and we had about two, three minutes with father.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And there were some prisoners which were still quite able-bodied, not like the one I'm describing.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And they kept on telling us, say you are older, and say you can work.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "That's what they kept on telling us.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "We didn't know what it was all about.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And they were separating the women from the men.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "We embraced with father, and we said to him-- he said to us, this is it.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "We meet after the war in the apartment in Prague.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "We embraced.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "We kissed, and that was the last time I saw my father.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "Now there was a line of men.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "I never saw my father.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And then there was a line, long line, of women too.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "I mean, this was a whole big, and this came all from Theresienstadt.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "Now what I want to point out is in Theresienstadt, the atmosphere was you knew everybody and you were friends or you knew them and were acquaintances or heard of them and so on and so forth.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "Now we are entering an era where you do not know nobody.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "You do not know the languages which are being spoken around you.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "You are like, I would imagine, a Babylon-- you know, extracted.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And finishing in the line must have been another transport which I wouldn't know because all of a sudden there were people around us which we did not know.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And we waited and we waited.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "And slowly, slowly, it was moving up.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "Little did I know that at the end of the line is Mengele, which we learned much, much later on.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "All we saw-- we held hands, mother, and my sister and myself, my mother very observant.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
